1
00:00:03,637 --> 00:00:06,406
[SHIROE, VOICE‐OVER] THIS WORLD
HAS ONE TYPE OF CURRENCY: GOLD.

2
00:00:06,507 --> 00:00:08,341
[SHIMMER]

3
00:00:08,441 --> 00:00:10,677
[CORK POPS]
THE STANDARD COST FOR
THE ITEMS IN A SINGLE MEAL

4
00:00:10,777 --> 00:00:12,412
IS AROUND 5 GOLD.

5
00:00:12,513 --> 00:00:16,016
A NIGHT AT A CHEAP INN
IS 10 GOLD.

6
00:00:16,116 --> 00:00:19,285
SO BASICALLY IT TAKES
ABOUT 35 GOLD PER DAY

7
00:00:19,385 --> 00:00:21,588
TO TAKE CARE OF
LIFE'S NECESSITIES.

8
00:00:21,688 --> 00:00:22,789
IT'S NOT THAT HARD.

9
00:00:22,889 --> 00:00:26,059
JUST BEAT 6 GOBLINS
IN COMBAT.

10
00:00:26,159 --> 00:00:28,461
AND ADVENTURERS CAN PUT
THEIR MONEY AND ITEMS

11
00:00:28,562 --> 00:00:31,565
IN THE BANK LOCATED
IN THE GUILD BUILDING.

12
00:00:31,665 --> 00:00:35,001
THIS PREVENTS OTHER
PLAYERS FROM STEALING IT.

13
00:00:35,101 --> 00:00:36,436
NOW, OF COURSE,

14
00:00:36,537 --> 00:00:41,107
EACH PLAYER ONLY GETS
LIMITED SPACE.

15
00:00:41,207 --> 00:00:44,911
[SHIROE] I'M GONNA NEED
SOME MONEY TO MAKE IT WORK.

16
00:00:45,011 --> 00:00:46,547
5 MILLION IN GOLD.

17
00:00:46,647 --> 00:00:49,315
SHIROE, EVEN IF WE
CASHED IN ALL OUR GOODS,

18
00:00:49,415 --> 00:00:52,085
CRESCENT MOON'S TREASURY
WOULD ONLY HAVE 60,000.

19
00:00:52,185 --> 00:00:53,453
SERIOUSLY, SHIROE!

20
00:00:53,554 --> 00:00:55,488
LIKE, WHAT'S ALL
THE MONEY FOR?

21
00:00:55,589 --> 00:00:56,690
HM.

22
00:02:30,951 --> 00:02:33,153
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

23
00:02:34,921 --> 00:02:36,456
[GRUNTING]

24
00:02:36,557 --> 00:02:39,325
[SHORYU] YOU KNOW
THESE ARE EASIER TO
KILL THAN CATCH, RIGHT?

25
00:02:39,425 --> 00:02:40,794
[NAOTSUGU]
YEAH, AND IF
YOU KILL THEM,

26
00:02:40,894 --> 00:02:43,764
THEY JUST GO
AND TURN INTO
INGREDIENT ITEMS.

27
00:02:43,864 --> 00:02:45,165
RIDICULOUS.

28
00:02:45,265 --> 00:02:47,367
HOW IN THE HELL
DOES 200 KILOS OF
PORK OVER HERE

29
00:02:47,467 --> 00:02:49,202
TURN INTO ONLY
2 KILOGRAMS OF FOOD?

30
00:02:49,302 --> 00:02:51,337
[NAOTSUGU]
RIGHT? THAT'S WHY
WE'RE CATCHING THEM.

31
00:02:51,437 --> 00:02:53,039
IF YOU GET A GOOD CHEF
IN YOUR KITCHEN,

32
00:02:53,139 --> 00:02:54,508
HE CAN USE THE
WHOLE THING!

33
00:02:54,608 --> 00:02:56,376
(GROWLING)

34
00:02:56,476 --> 00:03:00,013
SUEY, BOYS!
LET'S DO THIS!

35
00:03:00,113 --> 00:03:01,948
OUR QUOTA FOR
TODAY IS 60.

36
00:03:02,048 --> 00:03:03,116
[HIEN] RIGHT.

37
00:03:03,216 --> 00:03:04,818
COOL! IF IT'S
FOR MARIELLE,

38
00:03:04,918 --> 00:03:06,953
I'LL GET ALL 60 MYSELF!

39
00:03:11,725 --> 00:03:13,226
UM...

40
00:03:13,326 --> 00:03:14,761
[LILIANA]
DOES THAT SEEM
A LITTLE BIT TIGHT?

41
00:03:14,861 --> 00:03:17,664
[ASHLIN]
SOMETHING EASIER TO
MOVE IN WOULD BE NICER.

42
00:03:17,764 --> 00:03:20,934
[ASUKA] COME ON, YOU GUYS,
LET'S SEE IF WE HAVE ANY
CLOTHES IN THE BANK.

43
00:03:21,034 --> 00:03:22,268
[ASHLIN] OK!

44
00:03:22,368 --> 00:03:24,104
CAN YOU TAKE A
TASTE OF THIS, CHIEF?

45
00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:26,540
[NYAN‐TA] AH, LET'S
HAVE A LOOK HERE.

46
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:28,909
HMM. IT COULD USE
SOME SALT...

47
00:03:29,009 --> 00:03:33,046
AND MAYBE JUST A HINT
OF CORIANDER AS YOUR
SECRET INGREDIENT.

48
00:03:33,146 --> 00:03:34,948
[GHIROV]
RIGHT! THANK YOU!

49
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:38,351
OH! HE'S SO AWESOME!

50
00:03:44,124 --> 00:03:47,193
(FLIES BUZZING)

51
00:03:47,293 --> 00:03:48,328
(MARIELLE SIGHS)

52
00:03:48,428 --> 00:03:51,497
I HAVEN'T LEFT THE
ROOM FOR 3 DAYS.

53
00:03:52,432 --> 00:03:54,735
I CAN'T TAKE
THIS ANYMORE.

54
00:03:54,835 --> 00:03:57,804
AND WE NEED TO HAVE
ALL OF THESE REGISTERS
APPROVED ALSO.

55
00:03:57,904 --> 00:03:59,773
DOUBLE‐CHECK THE
FIGURES BEFORE WE
ASSUME THE MONEY'S THERE.

56
00:03:59,873 --> 00:04:02,576
[MARIELLE]
WAIT! IT'S IMPOSSIBLE.
THAT'S TOTALLY IMPOSSIBLE!

57
00:04:02,676 --> 00:04:04,344
[HENRIETTA] OH, I'M
SURE YOU'LL DO FINE.

58
00:04:04,444 --> 00:04:07,648
YOU KNOW MATH AND
PAPERWORKY STUFF
ISN'T REALLY MY THING.

59
00:04:07,748 --> 00:04:09,282
[MARIELLE] YOU'RE
THE GUILD MASTER,

60
00:04:09,382 --> 00:04:10,817
SO YOU'RE SUPPOSED
TO APPROVE THE BUDGET.

61
00:04:10,917 --> 00:04:13,286
[MARIELLE] SHUT UP! SHUT UP!
SHUT YOUR FACE, UMEKO!

62
00:04:13,386 --> 00:04:15,455
[HENRIETTA] UGH!
DON'T USE MY REAL NAME!

63
00:04:15,556 --> 00:04:17,891
[MARIELLE] UMEKO! UMEKO! UMEKO!
[HENRIETTA] HNG!

64
00:04:17,991 --> 00:04:19,826
(THUD)
[BOTH] HUH?

65
00:04:19,926 --> 00:04:21,595
I'VE BROUGHT MORE, MARIELLE.

66
00:04:21,695 --> 00:04:23,764
[MARIELLE]
SHIROE, YOU'RE, LIKE,
TOTALLY THE DEVIL.

67
00:04:23,864 --> 00:04:27,534
I'VE GONE AHEAD AND COMPILED
A LIST OF EVERYTHING YOU
REQUESTED FROM US.

68
00:04:27,634 --> 00:04:30,370
[SHIROE]
NOW, THAT WAS QUICK. HMM.

69
00:04:30,470 --> 00:04:31,805
THE NUMBERS LOOK
ACCURATE, TOO.

70
00:04:31,905 --> 00:04:34,541
OUR TREASURER IS
A FRICKIN' PIECE OF WORK.

71
00:04:34,641 --> 00:04:37,143
IT'S LIKE SHE
ENJOYS TORTURING
HERSELF WITH BUNCHES

72
00:04:37,243 --> 00:04:38,512
OF STUPID NUMBERY CRAP.

73
00:04:38,612 --> 00:04:40,280
NO. I'M JUST GOOD
WITH TAKING CARE

74
00:04:40,380 --> 00:04:42,248
OF THE BOOKKEEPING,
MARIELLE DARLING.

75
00:04:42,348 --> 00:04:43,817
WHAT REALLY MAKES
THIS SPECTACULAR IS

76
00:04:43,917 --> 00:04:46,853
HOW MERCILESS SHIROE'S PLAN
IS TURNING OUT TO BE.

77
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:49,355
HE OUGHT TO HAVE EVERYONE HE
MEETS START ADDRESSING HIM

78
00:04:49,455 --> 00:04:50,891
AS "MR. SUPERVILLAIN."

79
00:04:50,991 --> 00:04:53,627
THIS PLAN MIGHT QUALIFY
ME TO BE A SUPERVILLAIN,

80
00:04:53,727 --> 00:04:56,396
BUT IT'S NOTHING LIKE
MARIELLE'S PAPERWORK SKILLS.

81
00:04:56,496 --> 00:04:58,164
[HENRIETTA] I AGREE
WITH THAT. HA HA!

82
00:04:58,264 --> 00:04:59,299
(SHIROE LAUGHING)

83
00:04:59,399 --> 00:05:01,301
[MARIELLE] I GIVE UP.

84
00:05:01,401 --> 00:05:02,603
(HENRIETTA SIGHS)

85
00:05:02,703 --> 00:05:04,505
THE WORKLOAD REALLY
IS TAXING.

86
00:05:04,605 --> 00:05:06,540
I'M AFRAID I'M
GOING TO NEED OUR DEAR
LITTLE AKATSUKI AROUND

87
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,208
TO KEEP ME GOING ALL
THROUGH THE DAY.

88
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:11,545
I'M AFRAID I'VE GOT
HER DOING SOMETHING
ELSE FOR ME RIGHT NOW,

89
00:05:11,645 --> 00:05:13,647
BUT SHE MIGHT
HAVE A MINUTE.
[HENRIETTA] OH!

90
00:05:13,747 --> 00:05:16,116
HA HA. OH!

91
00:05:16,216 --> 00:05:18,084
(AKATSUKI SHUDDERS)

92
00:05:18,184 --> 00:05:22,856
I'M STUCK INSIDE A GAME SERVER,
SO HOW CAN I BE CATCHING A COLD?

93
00:05:22,956 --> 00:05:24,658
[MAN WITH SCARF] HERE'S THE
TAKE FOR THIS WEEK.

94
00:05:24,758 --> 00:05:26,426
THIS WAS A GREAT WAY
TO EARN MONEY.

95
00:05:26,527 --> 00:05:28,161
[MAN IN FEATHER CAP] HEH HEH!
THANKS FOR THE CASH, MAN.

96
00:05:28,261 --> 00:05:29,963
TELL ISAAC HELLO FOR ME.

97
00:05:30,063 --> 00:05:33,199
[MAN WITH SCARF] HEY, I HEARD
YOU STARTED DEALING IN
LEATHERWORKING, TOO.

98
00:05:33,299 --> 00:05:38,171
[MAN WITH FEATHER CAP]
24/7, MAN. WE GOT PEOPLE WORKING
AROUND THE CLOCK AND FAST, TOO.

99
00:05:38,271 --> 00:05:40,507
[NYAN‐TA] WELL, BLESS
ALL 9 OF MY LIVES.

100
00:05:40,607 --> 00:05:42,275
THIS IS QUITE A HAUL, YO.

101
00:05:42,375 --> 00:05:43,977
[NAOTSUGU] NOW IT'S
UP TO YOU, CHIEF.

102
00:05:44,077 --> 00:05:47,748
[MARIELLE] (SQUEALING)
OH! NAOTSUGU, THANK
YOU! THANK YOU!

103
00:05:47,848 --> 00:05:51,317
[NAOTSUGU] WHOA! OH,
COME ON. COME ON. COME ON.

104
00:05:51,417 --> 00:05:53,453
I'M NOT A BODY PILLOW,
YOU DINGBAT!

105
00:05:53,554 --> 00:05:55,656
MARIELLE, BEHAVE YOURSELF!

106
00:05:55,756 --> 00:05:58,324
SHORYU AND HIEN,
THANK YOU BOTH, TOO.

107
00:05:58,424 --> 00:05:59,826
[HIEN] HE SEEMED
REALLY MOTIVATED.

108
00:05:59,926 --> 00:06:03,163
[SHORYU] UH, NO, I JUST
OUTWORK YOU, YOU SLACKER!

109
00:06:03,263 --> 00:06:05,165
OH, WHATEVER,
LOVER BOY.

110
00:06:05,265 --> 00:06:06,533
LOYAL LITTLE
PUPPY DOG!

111
00:06:06,633 --> 00:06:08,702
DID A FOX JUST
CALL ME A DOG?!

112
00:06:08,802 --> 00:06:11,772
BUT, LIKE, THERE STILL
TOTALLY ISN'T ENOUGH.

113
00:06:11,872 --> 00:06:13,406
[BARKING]
[SHORYU] I'M ON IT!

114
00:06:13,507 --> 00:06:15,776
[AIRPLANE FLYBY]

115
00:06:15,876 --> 00:06:17,477
[MARIELLE] SHORYU'S
TOTALLY INTO THIS.

116
00:06:17,578 --> 00:06:19,513
I DON'T EVEN
UNDERSTAND IT.

117
00:06:19,613 --> 00:06:22,382
YOU GO GET THAT
MEAT, SHORYU!

118
00:06:22,482 --> 00:06:23,950
[HIEN CHUCKLES]

119
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:26,086
[WOLF HOWLING]

120
00:06:26,186 --> 00:06:27,621
[MARIELLE]
YOU ARE KILLING ME!

121
00:06:27,721 --> 00:06:29,656
[HENRIETTA] THIS IS
ALL THE PAPERWORK.

122
00:06:29,756 --> 00:06:33,627
NOW I CAN RETURN TO MY OWN JOB.

123
00:06:33,727 --> 00:06:36,396
YOU'RE JUST AN
EVIL PERSON.

124
00:06:36,496 --> 00:06:39,332
YOU AND SHIROE ARE DEMONS!

125
00:06:39,432 --> 00:06:41,334
[BOTH] READY FOR BUSINESS!

126
00:06:41,434 --> 00:06:43,236
[HENRIETTA]
OH, IT'S WONDERFUL!

127
00:06:43,336 --> 00:06:44,938
[LILIANA]
CUTE AND DISTINCTIVE.

128
00:06:45,038 --> 00:06:47,473
[ASUKA] OH, MY GOD. YOU GUYS,
THAT LOOKS ABSOLUTELY AMAZING!

129
00:06:47,574 --> 00:06:49,576
[LILIANA]
WE'RE ALMOST DONE NOW.

130
00:06:49,676 --> 00:06:53,514
[ASHLIN] AWW...
[HENRIETTA] IT'S FINALLY TIME.

131
00:06:53,614 --> 00:06:55,816
[SHIROE] WHAT DO YOU
THINK, HENRIETTA?

132
00:06:55,916 --> 00:06:57,350
[HENRIETTA] HMM?

133
00:06:57,450 --> 00:07:00,253
[SHIROE] I KNOW THAT YOU
MENTIONED YOU'RE AN
ACCOUNTANT WITH AN MBA.

134
00:07:00,353 --> 00:07:03,957
DO YOU THINK MY PLAN
HAS ANY MERIT AT ALL?

135
00:07:04,057 --> 00:07:05,759
[SHIROE] I THINK IT'S
GOT A GOOD CHANCE.

136
00:07:05,859 --> 00:07:08,394
ALL WE HAVE TO DO NOW IS
RAISE THE MONEY WE NEED

137
00:07:08,494 --> 00:07:09,930
AS QUICKLY AS WE CAN.

138
00:07:10,030 --> 00:07:12,432
[SHIROE] WE DON'T HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT WHERE IT CAME FROM

139
00:07:12,533 --> 00:07:14,801
OR EVEN WHO WAS GIVING IT TO US.

140
00:07:14,901 --> 00:07:18,438
RIGHT NOW WE'RE IN A TERRA NOVA
SITUATION WITH NO LAWS.

141
00:07:18,539 --> 00:07:22,208
SO LET'S NOT RESTRICT
OURSELVES BY MAKING UP
A BUNCH OF NEW ONES.

142
00:07:22,308 --> 00:07:23,544
[HENRIETTA] HMM.

143
00:07:23,644 --> 00:07:26,880
[HENRIETTA, THINKING]
THIS WORLD HAS NO RULES.

144
00:07:26,980 --> 00:07:30,884
IN OTHER WORDS,
WE CAN MAKE UP OUR OWN.

145
00:07:32,519 --> 00:07:35,622
WE NEED A NEW RULE
TO MAKE MONEY,

146
00:07:35,722 --> 00:07:40,060
A WAY TO MAKE PEOPLE BRING US
MONEY AND BE HAPPY DOING SO.

147
00:07:45,498 --> 00:07:47,100
WE CAN DO IT.

148
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,802
5 MILLION GOLD.

149
00:07:48,902 --> 00:07:51,938
WE CAN GET THE MONEY.
THERE'S NO DOUBT IN MY MIND.

150
00:07:52,038 --> 00:07:54,741
[MARIELLE] HUH?
[SHORYU] HUH? UH?

151
00:07:54,841 --> 00:07:56,009
(SHIMMER)

152
00:07:56,109 --> 00:07:57,811
(TING)

153
00:07:57,911 --> 00:08:01,515
[HENRIETTA] NOW IT'S TIME FOR
THE PLAN'S FIRST STAGE.

154
00:08:01,615 --> 00:08:04,585
[KNOCK ON DOOR]
[DOOR OPENS]

155
00:08:04,685 --> 00:08:06,553
[NAOTSUGU] HEY, MARIELLE,
I BROUGHT YOU A SNACK.

156
00:08:06,653 --> 00:08:10,591
CHIEF NYAN‐TA MADE THIS
SANDWICH HIMSELF. UH...

157
00:08:10,691 --> 00:08:13,193
[MARIELLE] I CAN'T DO IT.
STUPID UMEKO! I HATE HER!

158
00:08:13,293 --> 00:08:14,460
I HATE HER! I HATE HER!

159
00:08:14,561 --> 00:08:15,829
[NAOTSUGU] HO HO! HEY!
COME ON, NOW, EH‐

160
00:08:15,929 --> 00:08:18,098
I HATE PAPERWORK,
THIS ROOM, EVERYTHING!

161
00:08:18,198 --> 00:08:19,833
I WANT A BATH. I WANT TO GO
OUTSIDE. I WANT MY MOMMY!

162
00:08:19,933 --> 00:08:23,469
[NAOTSUGU] OK, OK, MARIELLE.
I'LL JUST SET THIS, UH...

163
00:08:23,570 --> 00:08:25,005
HERE YOU GO.

164
00:08:25,105 --> 00:08:26,339
MMM.

165
00:08:26,439 --> 00:08:28,542
MM! THIS IS GREAT!

166
00:08:28,642 --> 00:08:30,176
[NAOTSUGU] HEY, MARIELLE...
[MARIELLE] HMM?

167
00:08:30,276 --> 00:08:33,814
I THINK IT'S REALLY
GREAT YOU SIGNED OFF
ON SHIROE'S PLAN.

168
00:08:33,914 --> 00:08:34,981
HUH?

169
00:08:35,081 --> 00:08:36,883
[NAOTSUGU] IT WAS REALLY
SOMETHING SPECIAL TO HIM

170
00:08:36,983 --> 00:08:39,185
THAT YOU DECIDED TO
HELP HIM OUT AND ALL.

171
00:08:39,285 --> 00:08:41,855
SO, UH... SO THANKS A LOT.

172
00:08:41,955 --> 00:08:47,093
[MARIELLE] OH... YOU'RE SUCH
A GOOD BOY, NAOTSUGU.

173
00:08:48,128 --> 00:08:49,395
SUCH A GOOD BOY.

174
00:08:49,495 --> 00:08:50,897
EASY, NOW.

175
00:08:50,997 --> 00:08:53,600
YES, YOU ARE.
OH, YES, YOU ARE,
LITTLE NAOTSUGU.

176
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:56,236
I'M SO GLAD YOU'RE
HERE WITH SHIROE.

177
00:08:56,336 --> 00:08:59,005
YEAH. NO BIG DEAL.

178
00:08:59,105 --> 00:09:01,608
[NAOTSUGU] SO IT'S GOING
DOWN TOMORROW, HUH?

179
00:09:01,708 --> 00:09:04,210
[MARIELLE]
YEAH, TOMORROW.

180
00:09:08,414 --> 00:09:11,484
[DOLCHE] HEY, GUYS,
YOU WANT TO GET
SOMETHING TO MUNCH ON

181
00:09:11,585 --> 00:09:13,353
BEFORE WE HEAD OUT TO
THE HUNTING GROUNDS?

182
00:09:13,453 --> 00:09:14,888
[KAWARA]
YEAH, WHATEVER. I GUESS.

183
00:09:14,988 --> 00:09:16,790
IT'S ALL GONNA BE
TASTELESS GARBAGE ANYWAY.

184
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:19,626
[ISAMI] IT'S NOT LIKE
YOU HAD TO REMIND US.

185
00:09:19,726 --> 00:09:22,462
[KAWARA] WHAT'S THE DEAL?
THIS PLACE IS DESERTED.

186
00:09:22,563 --> 00:09:24,064
[DOLCHE]
LIKE, WHERE
IS EVERYBODY?

187
00:09:24,164 --> 00:09:26,399
[KAWARA] WELL, IF IT'S GONNA
BE BLAND, MIGHT AS WELL GET

188
00:09:26,499 --> 00:09:28,268
THE CHEAPEST BLAND
IN TOWN, RIGHT?

189
00:09:28,368 --> 00:09:29,469
[LYCOPENE YAWNS]

190
00:09:29,570 --> 00:09:31,437
SO ARE YOU SMELLING
WHAT I'M SMELLING?

191
00:09:31,538 --> 00:09:32,706
IT CAN'T BE.

192
00:09:32,806 --> 00:09:35,942
[MARIELLE]
HELLO, RESIDENTS
OF AKIHABARA!

193
00:09:36,042 --> 00:09:39,780
FOR THOSE OF YOU WHO MISS
REAL FOOD, WE HAVE GOOD NEWS.

194
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:43,183
NOW YOU CAN BRING GENUINE
FLAVOR BACK TO YOUR TABLE.

195
00:09:43,283 --> 00:09:46,720
THE CRESCENT MOON REFRESHMENT
STAND OPENS TODAY!

196
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:48,555
PLEASE, GIVE IT A TRY.

197
00:09:48,655 --> 00:09:52,559
[SERARA]
AH! THANK YOU. THANK YOU
FOR YOUR PURCHASE! THANK YOU!

198
00:09:52,659 --> 00:09:54,795
SERARA, HE HASN'T
EVEN ORDERED ANYTHING.

199
00:09:54,895 --> 00:09:56,963
15 GOLD PIECES
FOR A CRESCENT BURGER,

200
00:09:57,063 --> 00:09:59,833
18 GOLD FOR A CRISPY
CHICKEN STRIP BASKET,

201
00:09:59,933 --> 00:10:02,769
AND 5 GOLD FOR A FREAKIN'
BLACK ROSE TEA?

202
00:10:02,869 --> 00:10:05,038
[DOLCHE]
THAT'S PRETTY PRICEY,
DON'T YOU THINK?

203
00:10:05,138 --> 00:10:07,941
[KAWARA] TOTALLY.
AND THEY'RE REALLY OVERDOING THE
HARD SELL.

204
00:10:08,041 --> 00:10:09,710
[MARIELLE] HEY, MISTER,
[SMASH] HEY...

205
00:10:09,810 --> 00:10:11,845
[MARIELLE] WOULD YOU CARE TO BE
THE FIRST AND TRY ONE OUT?

206
00:10:11,945 --> 00:10:14,748
YOU'LL BE AMAZED AT HOW
YUMMY YUM‐YUM IT IS!

207
00:10:14,848 --> 00:10:16,683
YEAH. SURE.
WHY NOT?

208
00:10:16,783 --> 00:10:18,985
WHY DON'T YOU BRING OUT A
CRESCENT BURGER, SWEET CHEEKS,

209
00:10:19,085 --> 00:10:19,720
FOR HER?

210
00:10:19,820 --> 00:10:21,287
ARE YOU
KIDDING ME?

211
00:10:21,387 --> 00:10:22,756
HA HA!
THANK YOU!

212
00:10:22,856 --> 00:10:25,458
[MARIELLE] ONE CRESCENT
BURGER COMING RIGHT UP!

213
00:10:25,559 --> 00:10:27,293
[ALL] THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

214
00:10:27,393 --> 00:10:28,595
[CUSTOMER 1] IT SMELLS SO GOOD.

215
00:10:28,695 --> 00:10:29,596
[CUSTOMER 2] I'M NOT
BUYING THAT GREAT SMELL

216
00:10:29,696 --> 00:10:31,565
IS GREAT TASTE.

217
00:10:31,665 --> 00:10:32,799
[DOLCHE]
HMM, IT MAY LOOK GREAT,

218
00:10:32,899 --> 00:10:34,300
BUT IT'S GONNA TASTE
LIKE TOTAL POOPY.

219
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:36,269
[MARIELLE]
GIVE IT A TRY.

220
00:10:36,369 --> 00:10:37,604
(LYCOPENE SNIFFS)

221
00:10:37,704 --> 00:10:41,508
[LYCOPENE] MM! MM!

222
00:10:41,608 --> 00:10:42,843
[SMASH] WELL?

223
00:10:42,943 --> 00:10:44,811
[LYCOPENE] OH, MY GOD!
OH, MY GOD. MM!

224
00:10:44,911 --> 00:10:48,582
IT‐IT TOTALLY TASTES
LIKE A FREAKIN' HAMBURGER.
[SMASH] HUH?!

225
00:10:48,682 --> 00:10:51,151
[CUSTOMER 1] ALL RIGHT!
I WANT ONE!
[CUSTOMER 2] I WANT ONE, TOO!

226
00:10:51,251 --> 00:10:52,418
[CUSTOMER 3]
YEAH, GIVE ME A BURGER,
SWEET CHEEKS.

227
00:10:52,519 --> 00:10:53,854
[CUSTOMER 4] ME, TOO!

228
00:10:55,221 --> 00:10:58,491
[DOLCHE] SAUCY, MEATY, JUICY,
AND SIMPLY FABULOUS!

229
00:10:58,592 --> 00:11:00,627
[KAWARA]
IT'S FREAKING AWESOME.

230
00:11:00,727 --> 00:11:02,629
[ISAMI] I CAN EAT, LIKE,
10 OF THESE THINGS.

231
00:11:02,729 --> 00:11:03,997
[DOLCHE]
WE GOT TO TELL SOJI.

232
00:11:04,097 --> 00:11:06,032
[CUSTOMER 1] I'LL TAKE
3 CRESCENT BURGERS...

233
00:11:06,132 --> 00:11:08,902
[CUSTOMER 2]
5 CRISPY CHICKEN STRIPS.

234
00:11:09,002 --> 00:11:11,938
[CLOAKED CUSTOMER] I'LL TAKE
ONE OF EVERYTHING ON THE MENU.

235
00:11:12,038 --> 00:11:14,407
(CUSTOMERS ORDERING, INDISTINCT)

236
00:11:22,616 --> 00:11:23,817
(WOOD RATTLING)

237
00:11:23,917 --> 00:11:26,219
[SERARA] UM, UM, THIS IS
THE END OF THE LINE!

238
00:11:26,319 --> 00:11:29,923
THANK YOU FOR STAYING IN
PLACE AND NOT SKIPPING AHEAD!

239
00:11:30,023 --> 00:11:31,692
[ASUKA] WE ONLY HAVE
ONE BOX OF BURGERS LEFT!

240
00:11:31,792 --> 00:11:33,259
[MARIELLE]
WHAT? REALLY?!

241
00:11:33,359 --> 00:11:35,796
DON'T WORRY YOUR PRETTY
LITTLE HEAD, MARIELLE.

242
00:11:35,896 --> 00:11:38,331
MORE BURGERS ARE ON
THEIR WAY RIGHT NOW.

243
00:11:39,866 --> 00:11:43,203
[HENRIETTA] THIS IS WHERE WE
REALLY NEED TO GET GOING.

244
00:11:43,303 --> 00:11:46,907
GET READY TO REALLY
CRANK THEM OUT!

245
00:11:47,007 --> 00:11:51,477
[SOJIRO] WOW. THIS IS GOOD.
DO WE KNOW WHO MADE THIS?

246
00:11:51,578 --> 00:11:53,780
HOW DID THEY DO IT?

247
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:56,082
[CUSTOMER 1] HAVE YOU TRIED
THE CRESCENT BURGER YET?

248
00:11:56,182 --> 00:11:59,152
I HEARD IT'S FOOD THAT
ACTUALLY TASTES LIKE FOOD!

249
00:11:59,252 --> 00:12:02,455
[CUSTOMER 2] YOU MEAN IT
DOESN'T TASTE LIKE DOG CRAP?

250
00:12:02,556 --> 00:12:03,724
FOR REAL?

251
00:12:03,824 --> 00:12:05,959
[KARASHIN] SUCH FLAVOR
AT THIS PRICE?

252
00:12:06,059 --> 00:12:08,829
I WONDER WHAT IT'D TAKE TO GET
A PIECE OF THIS ACTION.

253
00:12:08,929 --> 00:12:12,098
[KAYU] WE GOT TROUBLE, CHIEF!
YOU GOT TO SEE THIS!

254
00:12:12,198 --> 00:12:14,935
[MICHITAKA] YOU'RE A LITTLE
LATE TO THE GAME, KAYU.

255
00:12:15,035 --> 00:12:16,436
BUT, YES, IT'S GOOD.

256
00:12:16,537 --> 00:12:17,638
MM! MM‐HMM.

257
00:12:17,738 --> 00:12:19,339
[MICHITAKA] KEEP AN
EYE ON THAT SHOP.

258
00:12:19,439 --> 00:12:22,175
FIND OUT WHO'S RUNNING
IT AND WHERE THEY GET
THEIR SUPPLIES FROM.

259
00:12:22,275 --> 00:12:24,845
[MICHITAKA] I MEAN IT.
FIND OUT EVERYTHING YOU CAN.

260
00:12:24,945 --> 00:12:26,112
[KAYU] RIGHT!
WILL DO, BOSS.

261
00:12:26,212 --> 00:12:29,850
[MICHITAKA] NOW, THAT'S
A TASTY BURGER.

262
00:12:32,553 --> 00:12:34,287
(BOAR GROWLING)

263
00:12:34,387 --> 00:12:36,790
[NAOTSUGU] RIGHT. THAT
OUGHT TO DO US FOR NOW.

264
00:12:36,890 --> 00:12:38,859
LET'S BOUNCE, OK?
COME ON.

265
00:12:38,959 --> 00:12:41,528
[HIEN] YOU GOT IT.
[SHORYU] I'M GONNA GO HUNT
DOWN SOME MORE, ALL RIGHT?

266
00:12:41,628 --> 00:12:42,796
[NAOTSUGU] HUH?

267
00:12:42,896 --> 00:12:44,230
[SHORYU] YOU GUYS CAN
GO BACK IF YOU WANT.

268
00:12:44,330 --> 00:12:46,633
[NAOTSUGU] DUDE, YOU DON'T
HAVE TO KILL YOURSELF.

269
00:12:46,733 --> 00:12:48,669
SLOW AND STEADY
GETS THE PIG.

270
00:12:48,769 --> 00:12:51,237
I AM NOT
GONNA LOSE.

271
00:12:51,337 --> 00:12:52,806
HUH? LOSE WHAT, DUDE?

272
00:12:52,906 --> 00:12:54,641
LET HIM GO AND KNOCK
HIMSELF OUT.

273
00:12:54,741 --> 00:12:55,942
ARE YOU SURE
ABOUT THAT?

274
00:12:56,042 --> 00:12:58,444
HE'S NOT LISTENING ANYWAY.

275
00:12:58,545 --> 00:12:59,713
[SHORYU] I'M GOING.

276
00:12:59,813 --> 00:13:02,315
FOR MY MARIELLE, ANYTHING.

277
00:13:02,415 --> 00:13:03,183
(GROWLING)

278
00:13:03,283 --> 00:13:07,420
[SHORYU]
HOLY CRAP!
A... A...

279
00:13:07,521 --> 00:13:10,223
A GIANT BOAR...

280
00:13:11,391 --> 00:13:13,627
[SHIROE] ALL RIGHT, YOU GUYS.
REALLY GOOD WORK.

281
00:13:13,727 --> 00:13:14,995
[MARIELLE] COME ON.
LIKE, COME ON!

282
00:13:15,095 --> 00:13:16,396
LIKE, WHAT DID WE MAKE?

283
00:13:16,496 --> 00:13:20,266
[HENRIETTA] WE EARNED
43,776 GOLD IN SALES.

284
00:13:20,366 --> 00:13:26,006
THAT'S 1,159 CUSTOMERS
WHO SPENT AN AVERAGE OF
38 GOLD PIECES EACH.

285
00:13:26,106 --> 00:13:28,909
[HENRIETTA] WE SOLD OUT THE
CRESCENT BURGERS WE PREPARED

286
00:13:29,009 --> 00:13:33,046
AS WELL AS EVERYTHING ELSE,
EXCEPT THE BLACK ROSE TEA.

287
00:13:33,146 --> 00:13:35,081
AWESOME! HA HA.
LIKE, THIS IS SO GREAT.

288
00:13:35,181 --> 00:13:39,720
LIKE, WE OUGHT TO HAVE THAT
5 MILLION GOLD IN NO TIME IF
WE KEEP DOING THIS BUSINESS.

289
00:13:39,820 --> 00:13:43,223
[SHIROE]
ACTUALLY, IT'S GONNA TAKE A LOT
MORE TIME THAN WE REALLY HAVE.

290
00:13:43,323 --> 00:13:44,891
HUH? IT WILL?

291
00:13:44,991 --> 00:13:48,094
[SHIROE] IT'D TAKE 120 MORE
DAYS BASED ON THOSE SALES.

292
00:13:48,194 --> 00:13:50,130
AND 4 MONTHS IS
WAY TOO LONG.

293
00:13:50,230 --> 00:13:53,934
[MARIELLE] THAT MIGHT BE,
BUT I KNOW WE, LIKE, TURNED
A LOT OF CUSTOMERS AWAY TODAY.

294
00:13:54,034 --> 00:13:55,301
I COULD PROBABLY
SELL A LOT MORE.

295
00:13:55,401 --> 00:13:57,671
LOOK, I KNOW WHERE
YOU'RE GOING WITH THIS.

296
00:13:57,771 --> 00:13:59,640
I KNOW OUR POTENTIAL
CUSTOMER BASE.

297
00:13:59,740 --> 00:14:03,977
[SHIROE] THERE ARE OVER 15,000
PLAYERS THAT WOULD EAT A
CRESCENT BURGER EVERY DAY.

298
00:14:04,077 --> 00:14:08,348
[HENRIETTA] THE PROBLEM IS
NO MATTER HOW HIGH THE
DEMAND HAPPENS TO GROW,

299
00:14:08,448 --> 00:14:12,819
WE CAN ONLY FEASIBLY SERVE
AROUND A THOUSAND CUSTOMERS
A DAY AND NOTHING MORE.

300
00:14:12,919 --> 00:14:15,388
OUR GUILD JUST
ISN'T BIG ENOUGH.

301
00:14:15,488 --> 00:14:16,590
(MARIELLE SIGHS)

302
00:14:16,690 --> 00:14:17,791
THAT'S PRETTY
MUCH IT.

303
00:14:17,891 --> 00:14:19,325
AND IF YOU REMEMBER,
MARIELLE,

304
00:14:19,425 --> 00:14:20,994
THIS WASN'T ABOUT STAYING
IN BUSINESS AND MAKING MONEY.

305
00:14:21,094 --> 00:14:22,996
OH, THAT'S
RIGHT! HA HA!

306
00:14:23,096 --> 00:14:25,899
I GUESS ALL THOSE GOLD PIECES
WERE STARTING TO BLIND ME.

307
00:14:25,999 --> 00:14:27,634
(LAUGHING)

308
00:14:27,734 --> 00:14:30,937
I'LL JUST GO DEPOSIT EVERYTHING
WE EARNED TODAY IN THE BANK.

309
00:14:31,037 --> 00:14:32,438
[SHIROE] THANKS.
[HENRIETTA] UH‐HUH.

310
00:14:32,539 --> 00:14:34,174
[MARIELLE] OK, SHIROE, SINCE
WE CAN'T GET ALL THE MONEY

311
00:14:34,274 --> 00:14:36,376
WITH THE CRESCENT BURGER,
DO WE DO YOUR OTHER PLAN?

312
00:14:36,476 --> 00:14:39,913
YOU KNOW, SO, LIKE,
WE'LL HAVE ENOUGH.

313
00:14:40,814 --> 00:14:42,248
[SHIROE]
OH, YEAH, IT'LL WORK.

314
00:14:42,348 --> 00:14:45,285
BUT, LIKE, I REALLY
DON'T KNOW IF I CAN.

315
00:14:45,385 --> 00:14:48,822
REMEMBER, HENRIETTA'S
GOT YOU COVERED ON
THE HARD PART.

316
00:14:48,922 --> 00:14:50,123
ISN'T THAT RIGHT?

317
00:14:50,223 --> 00:14:53,459
[HENRIETTA] YES.
LEAVE IT TO ME, OK?

318
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:55,495
IN EXCHANGE...

319
00:14:55,596 --> 00:14:56,830
UH!

320
00:14:56,930 --> 00:14:58,865
(HENRIETTA LAUGHING)

321
00:14:58,965 --> 00:15:01,401
[HENRIETTA] WHERE DO YOU
THINK YOU'RE GOING?!

322
00:15:01,502 --> 00:15:04,070
[AKATSUKI] OH, MY LORD HAS GIVEN
ME A SECRET MISSION TO EXECUTE!

323
00:15:04,170 --> 00:15:06,773
DON'T TRY STOPPING ME! AH!

324
00:15:06,873 --> 00:15:09,843
[HENRIETTA] SHIROE WAS KIND
ENOUGH TO LEND YOU TO ME.

325
00:15:09,943 --> 00:15:11,444
ISN'T THAT JUST WONDERFUL?

326
00:15:11,545 --> 00:15:15,749
MY LORD, I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU SOLD ME OUT AGAIN!

327
00:15:15,849 --> 00:15:18,384
NOW, HURRY. PUT THIS ON!

328
00:15:18,484 --> 00:15:22,055
[AKATSUKI] NO WAY!
I'M NOT SOME LITTLE DOLL
FOR YOU TO DRESS UP!

329
00:15:22,155 --> 00:15:23,990
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)

330
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:25,892
[HENRIETTA] AH, AH, AH!

331
00:15:25,992 --> 00:15:27,528
YOU CAN'T ENTER THAT ROOM.

332
00:15:27,628 --> 00:15:29,129
[AKATSUKI]
WHAT'S THAT?

333
00:15:29,229 --> 00:15:32,298
[HENRIETTA] THIS ZONE BELONGS TO
THE CRESCENT MOON ALLIANCE.

334
00:15:32,398 --> 00:15:35,068
(BUZZING)
AND THAT WAREHOUSE ONLY
PERMITS GUILD MEMBERS.

335
00:15:35,168 --> 00:15:37,904
AND I'M SORRY, SWEETIE,
BUT ARE YOU A GUILD MEMBER?

336
00:15:38,004 --> 00:15:41,107
I GUESS I'LL
HAVE TO...

337
00:15:42,609 --> 00:15:44,678
(BUZZING)
[AKATSUKI] ARE YOU
FREAKING KIDDING ME?

338
00:15:44,778 --> 00:15:46,012
[HENRIETTA]
IT'S USELESS.

339
00:15:46,112 --> 00:15:48,815
I SET IT SO THAT SKILLS
CAN'T BE USED HERE.

340
00:15:48,915 --> 00:15:51,918
AND I CAN ALSO SET COMBAT
PERMISSIONS INDIVIDUALLY.

341
00:15:52,018 --> 00:15:53,687
CLEVER, RIGHT?

342
00:15:53,787 --> 00:15:57,290
(AKATSUKI WHIMPERING)

343
00:15:57,858 --> 00:15:59,059
(SQUEALS)

344
00:15:59,159 --> 00:16:00,694
[ASUKA, LILIANA, AND ASHLIN]
YOU'RE SO CUTE!

345
00:16:00,794 --> 00:16:04,497
[NYAN‐TA] WELL, I'LL BE.
IT LOOKS ABSOLUTELY
FETCHING ON YOU.

346
00:16:04,598 --> 00:16:08,301
DEAR GOD! I'M FREAKING
OUT ON THE CUTENESS!

347
00:16:08,401 --> 00:16:11,071
HEY, HAVE ANY OF
YOU SEEN SHORYU?
[HENRIETTA] HM?

348
00:16:11,171 --> 00:16:12,806
HE SHOULD HAVE
BEEN DONE ALREADY.

349
00:16:12,906 --> 00:16:17,210
HE WANTED THE BIG
GAME, SO HE PROBABLY
ISN'T BACK YET.

350
00:16:17,310 --> 00:16:20,013
LIKE, REALLY? I HOPE
HE'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

351
00:16:20,113 --> 00:16:21,748
[RUMBLING]
OHH...

352
00:16:21,848 --> 00:16:23,449
[LILIANA] OH, MY GOODNESS!

353
00:16:23,550 --> 00:16:26,119
[ASUKA] UM, THERE'S A GIANT
BOAR STUCK IN THE HALLWAY.

354
00:16:26,219 --> 00:16:28,254
[HIEN]
TH‐THAT'S A LOT OF PIG!

355
00:16:28,354 --> 00:16:32,826
MISS MARIELLE, IS THIS
GONNA HELP THE KITCHEN ANY?

356
00:16:32,926 --> 00:16:37,163
[SHORYU] UGH!
[MARIELLE] SHORYU! SHORYU!

357
00:16:37,263 --> 00:16:39,499
(SHORYU BREATHING DEEPLY)

358
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:42,769
HE SAID HE HADN'T HAD
ANY SLEEP FOR A WHILE.

359
00:16:42,869 --> 00:16:45,071
YEAH, THAT'S TRUE.

360
00:16:45,171 --> 00:16:47,508
OH, POOR GUY.

361
00:16:47,608 --> 00:16:50,076
[MARIELLE] THANKS FOR
YOUR HELP, EVERYONE.

362
00:16:50,176 --> 00:16:53,179
COMPANIONS LIKE YOU
ARE REALLY A BLESSING.

363
00:16:53,279 --> 00:16:55,782
[HIEN] FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH,
HE LOOKS HAPPY THAT WAY,

364
00:16:55,882 --> 00:16:57,283
ALMOST DEAD OR NOT.

365
00:16:57,383 --> 00:16:59,853
WELL, I HATE TO CAST
ASPERSIONS ON ALL
YOUR HARD WORK,

366
00:16:59,953 --> 00:17:05,692
BUT THE FLAVOR OF A GIANT
BOAR IS ENTIRELY TOO
STRONG FOR WHAT WE DO.

367
00:17:05,792 --> 00:17:07,293
(LAUGHTER)

368
00:17:07,393 --> 00:17:10,831
[MARIELLE] SHH! YOU'RE GONNA
TOTALLY WAKE HIM UP.

369
00:17:10,931 --> 00:17:17,137
[SHIROE]
EVERYONE IN CRESCENT MOON IS
SO FRIENDLY AND WELL‐MANNERED.

370
00:17:18,839 --> 00:17:22,375
[SHIROE]
REALLY. THERE'S HENRIETTA
AND MARIELLE.

371
00:17:22,475 --> 00:17:27,380
THEIR KINDNESS AND GLOWING
SMILES ARE INSPIRING
AND CONTAGIOUS.

372
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:32,452
ON TOP OF THAT, I FINALLY WENT
AND CREATED MY VERY OWN GUILD.

373
00:17:32,553 --> 00:17:35,589
I'LL MAKE SURE YOU GET
TO MEET THEM SOON.

374
00:17:36,890 --> 00:17:39,560
WE'RE GETTING
EVERYTHING READY.

375
00:17:39,660 --> 00:17:43,229
JUST HAVE A LITTLE FAITH,
AND WE'LL GET THIS DONE.

376
00:17:43,797 --> 00:17:45,231
(MINORI WHINCES)

377
00:17:48,368 --> 00:17:51,838
[SHIROE]
YOU'RE GONNA BE FINE.
I SWEAR IT.

378
00:17:51,938 --> 00:17:54,207
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)
OH!

379
00:17:54,307 --> 00:17:56,409
(SHIROE CLEARS THROAT)

380
00:18:05,151 --> 00:18:08,254
[TOYA] SHIROE SAID THAT?
[MINORI] YEAH.

381
00:18:09,455 --> 00:18:12,092
[TOYA]
WELL, ALL RIGHT, THEN.

382
00:18:12,192 --> 00:18:14,227
[MINORI] IS IT OK?
[TOYA] HMM?

383
00:18:14,327 --> 00:18:18,665
SERIOUSLY? IS ALL
THIS REALLY OK?

384
00:18:21,935 --> 00:18:23,970
[SHIROE]
THIS IS STRANGE, CHIEF.

385
00:18:24,070 --> 00:18:25,371
BACK WHEN I WAS PLAYING,

386
00:18:25,471 --> 00:18:27,373
ALL OF THESE BUILDINGS
WERE BACKGROUND ART.

387
00:18:27,473 --> 00:18:30,210
BUT NOW THE HUD SAYS THE
ZONES ARE ALL FOR SALE.

388
00:18:30,310 --> 00:18:32,245
[NYAN‐TA]
IT SEEMS THAT WAY, HMM?

389
00:18:32,345 --> 00:18:33,647
[SHIROE]
THAT'S NOT ALL EITHER.

390
00:18:33,747 --> 00:18:37,718
EVERY CITY AND BUILDING IN
THE WORLD IS FOR SALE.

391
00:18:37,818 --> 00:18:40,086
THE PRICES ARE JUST
OUTRAGEOUSLY HIGH.

392
00:18:40,186 --> 00:18:42,889
[NYAN‐TA] AND IN LIGHT
OF THE FACT THAT YOU
NEED A SMALL FORTUNE

393
00:18:42,989 --> 00:18:44,490
TO BUY A BUILDING
AROUND HERE,

394
00:18:44,591 --> 00:18:47,761
MAYBE TOKYO STATION SHOULD
BE OUR HEADQUARTERS, HMM?

395
00:18:47,861 --> 00:18:50,463
[SHIROE] NOT QUITE.

396
00:18:53,133 --> 00:18:55,602
(OWL HOOTING)
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

397
00:18:58,004 --> 00:18:59,540
[SOJIRO]
YOU GUYS WAIT LONG?

398
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:03,677
MASTER SHIROE, MASTER NYAN‐TA,
IT'S BEEN QUITE A WHILE.

399
00:19:03,777 --> 00:19:06,680
[SHIROE] HEY, SOJIRO.
[NYAN‐TA] HEY, LITTLE MAN.

400
00:19:06,780 --> 00:19:09,616
I HEARD YOU WENT AND STARTED
YOUR OWN GUILD, HMM?

401
00:19:09,716 --> 00:19:13,319
[SOJIRO] YUP. IT'S CALLED
THE BRIGADE OF THE WEST WIND.

402
00:19:13,419 --> 00:19:14,621
[SHIROE] IT'S SMALL,

403
00:19:14,721 --> 00:19:16,422
BUT SOJIRO'S BRIGADE
OF THE WEST WIND

404
00:19:16,523 --> 00:19:19,726
IS JUST AS POWERFUL AS THE
BIGGEST GUILDS OUT THERE.

405
00:19:19,826 --> 00:19:20,727
[NYAN‐TA] MEOW?

406
00:19:20,827 --> 00:19:22,162
[SOJIRO] NOT REALLY.

407
00:19:22,262 --> 00:19:24,464
WE WERE JUST GETTING OUR
FEET WET STARTING THE GUILD.

408
00:19:24,565 --> 00:19:27,668
THEN THE APOCALYPSE CAME AROUND
AND REWROTE ALL OUR PRIORITIES.

409
00:19:27,768 --> 00:19:30,370
I HONESTLY HADN'T BEEN KEEPING
UP WITH THINGS AS MUCH

410
00:19:30,470 --> 00:19:33,607
OR LOGGING IN AS OFTEN
SINCE THE TEA PARTY BROKE UP.

411
00:19:33,707 --> 00:19:37,911
ARE YOU STILL KEEPING
COMPANY WITH THAT DELIGHTFUL
NAZNA AND MISS SAKI?

412
00:19:38,011 --> 00:19:39,580
YEAH! NAZNA'S IN MY GUILD.

413
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:42,382
AND SHE'S JUST AS EASYGOING
AS SHE EVER WAS.

414
00:19:42,482 --> 00:19:44,651
SAKI WAS ALSO IN
THE GUILD WITH US,

415
00:19:44,751 --> 00:19:48,254
BUT I GUESS SHE DIDN'T LOG
IN DURING THE DAY OF
THE APOCALYPSE.

416
00:19:48,354 --> 00:19:50,356
SO WHILE I'M STILL
THINKING ABOUT IT,

417
00:19:50,456 --> 00:19:51,925
WOULD YOU HAPPEN
TO BE A...

418
00:19:52,025 --> 00:19:54,494
ARE YOU STILL AS POPULAR WITH
THE GIRLS AS YOU USED TO BE?

419
00:19:54,595 --> 00:19:57,263
[SOJIRO] HA HA. AH,
COME ON. I DON'T KNOW.

420
00:19:57,363 --> 00:19:59,533
[NYAN‐TA] AH! TO BE
YOUNG AGAIN. HA HA.

421
00:19:59,633 --> 00:20:01,401
[SOJIRO] SO TELL ME
SOMETHING, SHIROE,

422
00:20:01,502 --> 00:20:03,303
YOU FINALLY CALLED.

423
00:20:03,403 --> 00:20:06,206
WHAT INSPIRED YOU
TO GET IN TOUCH?

424
00:20:06,306 --> 00:20:07,908
[SHIROE]
WELL, YOU SEE‐

425
00:20:08,008 --> 00:20:09,442
[SOJIRO]
I GUESS WHAT
I MEAN IS,

426
00:20:09,543 --> 00:20:12,412
I THOUGHT YOU DIDN'T LIKE
ME OR SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

427
00:20:12,513 --> 00:20:14,781
HUH? WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

428
00:20:14,881 --> 00:20:20,020
[SOJIRO]
BECAUSE, WELL, I REMEMBER
ASKING YOU TO JOIN ME,

429
00:20:20,120 --> 00:20:22,355
BUT THEN YOU KIND OF
SAID "NO," YOU KNOW?

430
00:20:22,455 --> 00:20:24,124
[SHIROE] YEAH, BUT
IT WASN'T LIKE THAT.

431
00:20:24,224 --> 00:20:27,460
I LIKE YOU FINE, SOJIRO.

432
00:20:27,561 --> 00:20:29,896
I JUST DIDN'T FEEL
LIKE SPENDING ALL THAT
TIME BEING INVOLVED

433
00:20:29,996 --> 00:20:31,264
WITH A GUILD
BACK THEN.

434
00:20:31,364 --> 00:20:33,266
[SHIROE]
BUT HERE'S THE THING.

435
00:20:33,366 --> 00:20:36,036
THE APOCALYPSE MADE THIS
PLACE OUR REAL WORLD.

436
00:20:36,136 --> 00:20:38,672
AND SO THE WAY
WE LIVE HERE IS
GOING TO BE DIFFERENT

437
00:20:38,772 --> 00:20:41,041
THAN IT WAS WHEN
IT WAS JUST A GAME.

438
00:20:41,141 --> 00:20:46,279
[SHIROE] I CHOSE TO USE THE
POWER I HAVE TO PROTECT
PEOPLE WHO DON'T.

439
00:20:46,379 --> 00:20:48,549
I HAVE MADE A
GUILD OF MY OWN.

440
00:20:48,649 --> 00:20:50,350
WE'RE STARTING OUT,
AND WE'RE KIND OF SMALL.

441
00:20:50,450 --> 00:20:53,486
BUT IT'S NOT A BAD THING
WHEN YOU THINK ABOUT IT.

442
00:20:53,587 --> 00:20:56,489
BUT I'LL ONLY HAVE
A PLACE FOR MYSELF

443
00:20:56,590 --> 00:20:59,325
AFTER I'VE GIVEN OTHER
PEOPLE THE CHANCE.

444
00:21:00,393 --> 00:21:02,462
I THINK THAT'S FAIR.

445
00:21:03,196 --> 00:21:05,265
OH.

446
00:21:05,365 --> 00:21:07,968
SO THAT BRINGS ME BACK
TO WHY YOU CALLED ME.

447
00:21:08,068 --> 00:21:09,603
[NYAN‐TA]
WELL, MY FRIEND,

448
00:21:09,703 --> 00:21:13,139
WHAT WE WANT AT THE
MOMENT IS YOUR OPINION
OF AKIHABARA, HMM?

449
00:21:13,239 --> 00:21:17,844
[SOJIRO]
AH. IT'S LIKE A...
A PRISON.

450
00:21:17,944 --> 00:21:19,580
HONESTLY?

451
00:21:19,680 --> 00:21:21,815
[SOJIRO] IT'S NOT
JUST AKIHABARA.

452
00:21:21,915 --> 00:21:25,185
DEPENDING ON HOW YOU
LOOK AT IT, THE WHOLE
WORLD'S A PRISON.

453
00:21:25,285 --> 00:21:27,420
I MEAN, YOU CAN'T
EVEN DIE HERE.

454
00:21:27,521 --> 00:21:29,455
[SHIROE]
WELL, I KNOW WE CAN FIX IT.

455
00:21:29,556 --> 00:21:31,825
AND I NEED YOUR HELP.

456
00:21:34,194 --> 00:21:36,062
YEAH, I'M IN.

457
00:21:36,162 --> 00:21:37,598
HUH. YOU SURE?

458
00:21:37,698 --> 00:21:39,666
DON'T YOU WANT TO HEAR ABOUT
WHAT YOU'RE AGREEING TO FIRST?

459
00:21:39,766 --> 00:21:41,568
[SOJIRO] I DON'T THINK
THAT'LL BE NECESSARY.

460
00:21:41,668 --> 00:21:45,071
I JUST HAVE A FEELING IT'S
GONNA WORK OUT SOMEHOW.

461
00:21:45,171 --> 00:21:49,442
A SAMURAI'S JOB IS TO
FIGHT ON THE FRONT LINES
REGARDLESS OF THE PLAN.

462
00:21:49,543 --> 00:21:51,612
PLUS, BACK IN OUR TEA PARTY
DAYS, OUR STRATEGISTS ALWAYS

463
00:21:51,712 --> 00:21:55,048
SEEMED TO COME UP WITH SOMETHING
AMAZING TO GET US THROUGH.

464
00:21:55,148 --> 00:21:56,783
SOJIRO...

465
00:21:56,883 --> 00:22:00,020
[NYAN‐TA] YOU'RE ONE OF THE
GOOD ONES, LITTLE MAN.
ALWAYS HAVE BEEN.

466
00:22:00,120 --> 00:22:02,789
[SOJIRO] COME ON,
YOU GUYS. HA HA!

467
00:22:04,625 --> 00:22:06,593
I GOT MORE
BURGER MEAT HERE.

468
00:22:06,693 --> 00:22:08,094
[CUSTOMER]
3 CRESCENT BURGERS.

469
00:22:08,194 --> 00:22:09,530
ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY,

470
00:22:09,630 --> 00:22:11,431
LET ME COME AROUND AND GET
YOUR ORDER WHILE YOU WAIT.

471
00:22:11,532 --> 00:22:13,166
YOU'RE SO CUTE!

472
00:22:13,266 --> 00:22:14,701
OH, PLEASE ADD ME
TO YOUR FRIENDS' LIST.

473
00:22:14,801 --> 00:22:17,403
HEY, HOLD YOUR HORSES. HE SAID
HE WAS GONNA COME TO YOU.

474
00:22:17,504 --> 00:22:18,939
SERIOUSLY, BOSS?

475
00:22:19,039 --> 00:22:21,241
ARE YOU REALLY JUST GONNA
SIT OUT HERE ALL DAY LONG

476
00:22:21,341 --> 00:22:24,077
HOCKING BURGERS FOR
THIS SHIROE FELLA?

477
00:22:24,177 --> 00:22:25,646
[SOJIRO]
OF COURSE NOT.

478
00:22:25,746 --> 00:22:27,648
THERE'S A LOT MORE
TO IT THAN THIS.

479
00:22:27,748 --> 00:22:34,087
I HAVE FAITH IN HIS PLAN.
I KNOW HE CAN MAKE THIS RIGHT.

480
00:22:36,990 --> 00:22:41,828
